25 NEW SECTION. SECTION 2. GAMING IMPACT STUDY. (1) THE DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE, GAMBLING
26 CONTROL DIVISION, IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE GAMING ADVISORY COUNCIL, SHALL CONDUCT A STUDY OF THE GAMING
27 INDUSTRY IN MONTANA.
28 (2) THE STUDY MUST UTILIZE A RANGE OF DATA FROM DIFFERENT SOURCES, INCLUDING VIDEO GAMBLING
- 3 - Authorized Print Version – SB 150

- 2025
69th Legislature 2025 SB0150.2
1 MACHINE MANUFACTURERS, OWNERS, ROUTE OPERATORS, CASINO OWNERS, AND APPLICABLE TREND DATA FROM
2 MONTANA AND OTHER STATES.
3 (3) UPON COMPLETION OF THE STUDY, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PUBLISH A REPORT THAT IS ACCESSIBLE
4 TO THE PUBLIC. THE REPORT MUST INCLUDE:
5 (A) A COMPREHENSIVE ASSESSMENT OF THE DATA AS IT RELATES TO BET LIMITS, PAYOUT LIMITS, BONUS
6 GAMES, GAME STRUCTURE, AND OTHER ANCILLARY ISSUES THAT ARE DEEMED RELEVANT;
7 (B) SPECIFIC INFORMATION ABOUT THE METHODS USED FOR COLLECTING OR ACQUIRING DATA USED IN THE
8 REPORT; AND
9 (C) THE IDENTIFICATION OF SPECIFIC ISSUES FOR CONSIDERATION BY THE LEGISLATURE AND DEPARTMENT
10 CONCERNING GAMING.
11 (4) THE STUDY AND REPORT MUST BE COMPLETED BY DECEMBER 1, 2026.
